quran[10]{c,v,t}:
  23,23,"We sent Noah unto his people, and he said, \"O my people! Serve Allah, you have no God but Him; do you then not fear (evil)"
  23,24,"Said the chiefs of those who disbelieved among his people, \"This is nothing but a mortal like yourselves who wishes to make himself superior to you. Had Allah pleased He could surely have sent angels. We have not heard of this from our forefathers"
  23,25,He is nothing but a man possessed; so watch him for a while
  23,26,"Said he, \"My Lord! Help me, for they deny me"
  23,27,"And We inspired him, saying \"Make the ark under Our eyes and Our inspiration; and when the oven (of Allah´s wrath) boils over (or the fountains or springs of the earth are about to gush forth), conduct into it of every kind two spouses, and you"
  23,28,"But when you are settled, you and those with you in the ark, say, \"Praise belongs to Allah, Who saved us from the unjust people"
  23,29,"And say, ´My Lord! Cause me to land on a blessed landing place, for you are the best of all who bring to land.´"
  23,30,"Verily, in this is a sign, and, verily, We are ever trying them (mankind)"
  23,31,Then We raised up after them another generation
  23,32,"And We sent amongst them a messenger of their own (or from among them), saying, \"Serve Allah, you have no God but He; will you then not fear (evil)"